  <summary date="2018-03-15T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Veterans Mental Health Accessibility Act

This bill makes veterans who served on active duty in a theater of combat operations eligible for hospital care, medical services, and nursing home care for any mental illness through the Department of Veterans Affairs, notwithstanding insufficient medical evidence to conclude that the mental illness is attributable to such service.</summary>
